HEADWORD: Knight marshal
<hw>Knight" mar"shal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>An officer in the household of the British sovereign,
who has cognizance of transgressions within the royal household and
verge, and of contracts made there, a member of the household being one
of the parties.</def> <rj><au>Wharton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

